N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 12 ยง 803.28 - Finality for purposes of judicial review

State Regulations

Only a decision by the commissioner shall be deemed final
agency action for purposes of judicial review. A decision by a hearing officer
which becomes final for lack of appeal is not deemed final agency action for
purposes of article 78 of the Civil Practice Law and Rules. Notes
